<TITLE> Polls to be the major admin challenge: new cabinet secy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  Newly appointed cabinet secretary Md. Abdul Aziz on Thursday said the upcoming elections will be the biggest challenge his administration will have to face. His office was ready to help the Election Commission and the government in every way to ensure a free, fair election, he added. Outgoing cabinet secretary Ali Imam Majumder assured, "The present setup of the government is capable of holding the elections in a free, fair and credible way." The two spoke to reporters after the handover of office at the cabinet division on Thursday. Aziz, who was serving as secretary to the agriculture ministry, took charge of his new office Thursday afternoon. Majumder's tenure as cabinet secretary expires on Nov 28, but as it falls on the weekend, he bid bye on Thursday. Ali Imam handed to Abdul Aziz the conventional 'war-book' besides other files and documents. The outgoing secretary gave an account of his experience as a cabinet secretary during a significant turning point of the nation. On future challenges, Ali Imam said, "Challenges are always there and I believe the new administration will face them with skill and experience." The new cabinet secretary said the present administration's biggest task now would be to maintain law and order and help the EC hold a free and fair election. bdnew
